{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5dbf4e51-92ff-4ab7-a8bf-902291e2d874","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.**\n\nIn 3.x, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` defaulted to `false`, so the VSTest adapter was bundled and `vstest.console` worked. In 4.x it defaults to `true` — the project builds as a standalone executable using Microsoft.Testing.Platform, and the VSTest adapter is no longer included. That's why `vstest.console` finds zero tests.\n\n**You have two options:**\n\n1. **Recommended — switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (it supports both runners automatically) or invoke the test executable directly.\n\n2. **Quick fix — opt back into VSTest** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply either change to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"02431b34-f72f-4b4d-8b01-0a2a79008d2e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about what changed between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 that causes vstest.console to no longer discover tests. Let me provide the answer based on my knowledge.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new \"Microsoft Testing Platform\" runner). This means:\n\n1. In MSTest.Sdk/3.x, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` defaulted to `false`, so the VSTest adapter was included and vstest.console worked fine.\n\n\n2. In MSTest.Sdk/4.x, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` defaults to `true`, so the VSTest adapter is no longer included by default and vstest.console can't discover tests anymore. To fix this, you can either switch to `dotnet test` or the test executable directly, or explicitly set `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` to `false` in your project file.","outputTokens":547,"requestId":"0843:16A6CA:84935B3:93A1364:69EAD7B0"},"id":"fd7e2f59-7ac6-4826-9645-fd083fb1f8ad","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:38:51.955Z","parentId":"592b0649-0655-49b5-91d3-e28ffd7edc02"}
